quran[10]{c,v,t,f}:
  17,87,"except through a mercy from your Lord{1}; indeed, His grace upon you has been supreme.",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from 1st person to 3rd person.
  17,88,"Say, “Most surely, if all humans and all unseen beings{1}were to come together to bring forth the like of this Recital{2}, they could never bring forth the like of it, even if they backed up one another.”",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is jinnwhich are unseen beings that are accountable for their actions.The Arabic word used is Qur’anwhich literally means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.
  17,89,"And most surely, We have diversified for mankind in this Recital<a class=""sup""><sup>c </sup></a>every kind of parable, but most of mankind refused anything but constant denial."
  17,90,"And they said, “We will not believe in you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>until you make a spring gush forth from the ground for us;"
  17,91,"or possess a garden of palms and vines, then cause rivers to gush forth, pouring through them;"
  17,92,"or make the sky fall on us in pieces, as you claimed; or bring Allah and the angels before us;"
  17,93,"or possess a house of gold; or ascend into the sky. Even then, we will not believe in your ascension until you <span class=""h"">bestow</span>upon us <span class=""h"">from on high<sup foot_note=""80458"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>a scripture that we can read.” Say, “Highly Exalted is my Lord. Have I been anything except a human messenger?”"
  17,94,"And what prevented mankind from believing when guidance came to them, except that they said, “Did Allah send a human messenger?”"
  17,95,"<span class=""h"">Say<sup foot_note=""80459"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>, “If there were angels on earth walking around in peace, We would have bestowed upon them from heaven an angel messenger.”"
  17,96,"Say, “Allah is an adequate witness between you and me; indeed, He has always been All-Aware, All-Seeing of His servants.”"
